HEADWORD: onion dome
<hw>on`ion dome"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Architecture)</fld> <def>A dome with a pointed top, its width
often extending beyond the width of the tower it covers; -- a style of
architecture characteristic of Russian Orthodox churches.</def>⟦br⟧
